


tangent(1)                     Scilab Function                     tangent(1)






NAME
  tangent - linearization of a dynamical system at an equilibrium point

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [f,g,newm]=tangent(ff,xe,[ue])

PARAMETERS
  ff   : a string which gives the name of the Scilab macro which  codes  the
       system
  xe   : column vector which gives the equilibrium point for the value ue of
       the parameter
  ue   : real value.
  f, g : two matrices for the linearised  system  dxdot=f.dx + g.du
  newm : A new macro of type [y]=newm(t,x,u) which computes the field of the
       linearised system  (newm(t,xe,ue)=0)

DESCRIPTION
  linearises around the equilibrium point (xe,ue) the vector field of the
  dynamical system given by a Scilab macro ff, xdot=ff(t,x,[u]).  The dynami-
  cal system is supposed to be autonomous.




































